( 'external', 'external', 'Step One: Select Form', 'You can use major Wordpress form plugins to create constituent and activity records in WP Issues CRM from the front end.
WP Issues CRM will match the submitted form data into your database, creating new constituent records as needed for non-matching submissions.
<br/><br/>Select form type and select form (you must install the applicable form plugin and add the form first). <strong>We currently support: <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.gravityforms.com/">Gravity Forms</a> 
and <a  target="_blank" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/contact-form-7/">Contact Form 7</a></strong>.<br/><br/>', 10, 1, 0, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'defaults', 'Step Two: Classify Form Submissions', 'Select an issue (required) and activity type (optional) to classify submissions coming in through this form.', 20, 1, 0, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'types', 'Option: Data Types', 'Select phone/email/address types to be assigned to data coming in through this interface.', 45, 1, 1, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'assignments', 'Step Three: Map Form Fields', 'Please save/update basic selections from steps one and two before mapping fields.<br/><br/><button id="map_form_fields_button" class="wic-form-button">Map Form Fields</button>', 30, 1, 0, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'management', 'Option: Case Management', 'Select a staff member and case status to be assigned to constituents submitting data through this interface. Note that if a constituent has been previously
assigned to another staff member and the status is still open, the constituent will not be reassigned.  Either way, the review date will be set to today unless you leave the staff field blank.  If a constituent
is previously assigned and has an open status, that will not be removed, even if default status is not set for this interface.', 40, 1, 1, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'front_end_posts', 'Option: Front End Posts', 'You can use WP Issues CRM to create new Wordpress posts (and users) from forms. 
The new posts will be created as front facing posts on your site and the interface will log an activity record  for the new or existing constituent 
as for any other form submission.<br/><br/>
For new posts to be created, email_address, post_title and post_content must be mapped from the form and non-blank. It is up to the form to include and require those 
fields, otherwise new post/user creation will fail and insert an error message into the note on the activity created by the form interface. 
If new post creation fails, you will still get whatever notice the form sends.  
<br/><br/>User naming is controlled by the submitting form.  If a field keyed as `nick_name` is included in the form and is non-blank, it will be set as the display name for the new Wordpress user.  Otherwise, first and/or last name,
as mapped will be used.  However, there is no need to require any name at all.  A unique anonymous user name will be generated.<br/><br/>
This interface is designed to securely support transient users and returning users without requiring login for posting.  
Returning users who enter the same email address will see their display name remain constant across posts.
New Wordpress users will be created as Subscribers with no privileges and no password will be sent to them.  All user names, as opposed to display names, will include a 15 character random additional string and the password created 
for them is also hard to hack, 30 characters long with special characters. The site administrator can, of course,
create a usable login name and password (and reattribute posts to that usable login) through the Wordpress User interface.<br/><br/>
Control of spam submissions depends on the form.  The form plugins we support include spam control tools and we do encourage full use of those tools.', 50, 0, 1, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'update', 'Option: Update Policies for Existing Constituents', 'WP Issues CRM attempts to match incoming data to existing constituents
to avoid creating duplicates.  For unmatched constituents, all categories of incoming data will always be added, but, depending on the interface data source, you may want to set different policies on how incoming data will be applied
for matched constituents.  Note that constituent matching is attempted using field combinations in this order: (1) first name and email, (2) email alone, (3) first name, last name, street_address, (4)
first 5 letters of each of first name, full last name, street_address, (5) first name, last name, dob, (6) first name, last name, zip.', 60, 0, 1, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
( 'external', 'delete', 'Delete Form Interface', 'Deleting the interface will NOT delete the form and will NOT delete data previously captured through the form.', 100, 0, 1, '2000-01-01 01:01:01'),
